"The decision wasn't made with any ill intent towards Rizia. There are greater global forces at work than what's happening in our corner of South Merkopa."

"What the superpowers decide affects us, Mr. Esquibel. Their intent is of no importance."

"Care to catch me up?"

en


"SILENCE!"

All three fell silent. Laurento stared at me, somewhat taken aback.

en


"Excuse us, Your Majesty."

The three of them noticed me and fell silent.

"We were just discussing the recent news concerning Lespia's membership in ATO."

en


"I agree with Duchess Azaro. We should be very concerned."

"I agree with Mr. Esquibel. There's nothing to worry about."

en


"Why do you believe that, Your Majesty?"

en


"May I ask what makes you so certain?"

LineNo: 10127751,

Player_Romus: With Arcasia's backing, Lespia is...
en


"With Arcasia's backing, Lespia is bound to strengthen its grip on Pales."

LineNo: 10127853,

Player_Romus: Arcasia has a track record of sowi...
en


"Arcasia has a track record of sowing instability. We can't afford another uprising."

LineNo: 10127955,

Player_Romus: Lespia and Arcasia have been close...
en


"Lespia and Arcasia have been close for a decade. This just puts a name to it."

LineNo: 10128057,

Player_Romus: Southern Merkopa cannot be allowed...
en


"Southern Merkopa cannot be allowed to fall under the influence of superpowers. We ought to be our *own* superpower."

LineNo: 10128159,

Player_Romus: The superpowers won't touch us as...
en


"The superpowers won't touch us as long as we have Rumburg as an ally."

LineNo: 10128261,

Player_Romus: Lespia won't get too bold. Not wit...
en


"Lespia won't get too bold. Not with Valgsland and the CSP around to keep them in check."

LineNo: 10128363,

Laurento Esquibel: A very ambitious goal, considering...
en


"A very ambitious goal, considering how divided we are."

LineNo: 10128465,

Lucita Azaro: Which will certainly threaten the...
en


"Which will certainly threaten the tenuous peace we have established with both nations."

LineNo: 10128567,

Lucita Azaro: Rarely has ATO expanded without ch...
en


"Rarely has ATO expanded without chaos following close behind."

en


The day of my foreign policy council meeting had arrived, and it was a hot one.

LineNo: 10128771,

Narrator: I spent a while wandering around, t...
en


I spent a while wandering around, then returned to the middle of the garden, where a series of stone sculptures were surrounded by Rizian palms and succulents.

LineNo: 10128873,

Player_Romus: We don't know anything about the s...
en


"We don't know anything about the situation yet. We'll have to wait and see what happens."

LineNo: 10128975,

Hugo Toras: A reasonable response, Your Majest...
en


"A reasonable response, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10129077,

Lucita Azaro: Names have weight, Your Majesty. S...
en


"Names have weight, Your Majesty. So do atomic weapons."

LineNo: 10129179,

Lucita Azaro: Even worse, Your Majesty. That mea...
en


"Even worse, Your Majesty. That means Rizia is caught in the middle."

LineNo: 10129281,

Lucita Azaro: Queen Beatrice is already making o...
en


"Queen Beatrice is already making overtures towards Arcasia. With Queen Lena dead, which side do you think she'll take?"

LineNo: 10129383,

en


Laurento walked to the chamber's back wall and pulled down a map of southeastern Merkopa.

LineNo: 10129485,

Laurento Esquibel: What shall we discuss first?
en


"What shall we discuss first?"

LineNo: 10129587,

Player_Romus: We need to talk about Wehlen.
en


"We need to talk about Wehlen."

LineNo: 10129689,

Player_Romus: Isn't Pales the topic of the day?
en


"Isn't Pales the topic of the day?"

LineNo: 10129791,

Player_Romus: I haven't heard much about the cou...
en


"I haven't heard much about the countries of the former Empire of Moridia."

LineNo: 10129893,

Player_Romus: What's going on in Sordland?
en


"What's going on in Sordland?"

LineNo: 10129995,

Laurento Esquibel: Now that the Colonel has decided t...
en


"Now that the Colonel has decided to retire, you mean?"

LineNo: 10130097,

Laurento Esquibel: His successor is called Ewald Alph...
en


"His successor is called Ewald Alphonso. From everything I've heard, he's Soll's exact opposite."

LineNo: 10130223,

Player_Romus: That's good, right?
en


"That's good, right?"

LineNo: 10130325,

Player_Romus: What does that mean?
en


"What does that mean?"

LineNo: 10130427,

Player_Romus: Just a gut feeling.
en


"Just a gut feeling."

LineNo: 10130529,

Player_Romus: Just a feeling I have.
en


"Just a feeling I have."

LineNo: 10130631,

Lucita Azaro: Respectfully, Your Majesty, this c...
en


"Respectfully, Your Majesty, this council exists so that you may base your actions on more than mere gut feelings."

LineNo: 10130733,

Laurento Esquibel: What would you have us do, Duchess...
en


"What would you have us do, Duchess Azaro? We're on shaky enough ground with Lespia as it is."

LineNo: 10130835,

Lucita Azaro: Of course we should act sensibly....
en


"Of course we should act sensibly. But we need to show the Republic and its new friends that Rizia can hold its own."

LineNo: 10130937,

Laurento Esquibel: It depends. He's already institute...
en


"It depends. He's already instituted some major changes..."

LineNo: 10131039,

Laurento Esquibel: Think sweeping privatization and t...
en


"Think sweeping privatization and tax cuts. Sollists forced out of power. More women in prominent positions-- although he has yet to pass the kind of liberatory reforms our beloved Lyza did."

LineNo: 10131141,

Player_Romus: That's too bad. I actually liked S...
en


"That's too bad. I actually liked Soll."

LineNo: 10131243,

Laurento Esquibel: The feeling wasn't mutual. Soll's...
en


"The feeling wasn't mutual. Soll's disdain for the monarchy kept us shut out of trade negotiations with Sordland for decades."

LineNo: 10131345,

Laurento Esquibel: Do you want to discuss Morella? Or...
en


"Do you want to discuss Morella? Or Derdia?"

LineNo: 10131455,

Player_Romus: Derdia.
en


"Derdia."

LineNo: 10131557,

Player_Romus: Morella.
en


"Morella."

LineNo: 10131659,

Laurento Esquibel: Ah, yes. The only fully Golcondist...
en


"Ah, yes. The only fully Golcondist nation in the world."

LineNo: 10131761,

Laurento Esquibel: You've already heard about their n...
en


"You've already heard about their new left-wing ruling coalition, correct?"

LineNo: 10131863,

Narrator: Laurento rearranged some of the pap...
en


Laurento rearranged some of the papers he was holding.

LineNo: 10131965,

Laurento Esquibel: Of course.
en


"Of course."

LineNo: 10132067,

Laurento Esquibel: Relations with our onetime allies...
en


"Relations with our onetime allies have been turbulent at best since the civil war. The international unpopularity of current president Wiktor Smolak has only complicated matters."

LineNo: 10132193,

Player_Romus: My father made a deal with Wehlen...
en


"My father made a deal with Wehlen on good faith. Wehlen so far has respected the deal."

LineNo: 10132295,

Player_Romus: All I ask is that Wehlen return Zi...
en


"All I ask is that Wehlen return Zille as promised. After that, I'm happy to cut ties."

LineNo: 10132397,

Player_Romus: Rizia wouldn't be where we are tod...
en


"Rizia wouldn't be where we are today without Wehlen. We can't abandon our partnership."

LineNo: 10132499,

Player_Romus: It's not a good look for us to rem...
en


"It's not a good look for us to remain linked to them."

LineNo: 10132601,

Laurento Esquibel: It's not wrong. One might see it t...
en


"It's not wrong. One might see it that way."

LineNo: 10132703,

Laurento Esquibel: The return is scheduled for the en...
en


"The return is scheduled for the end of 1952, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10132805,

Laurento Esquibel: Rumburg in particular has been voc...
en


"Rumburg in particular has been vocal about ending the Smolak regime. But as long as Wehlen still holds Zille, diplomacy is key."

LineNo: 10132907,

Laurento Esquibel: Smolak has made nothing but enemie...
en


"Smolak has made nothing but enemies in the international arena, Rumburg chief among them. But yes, as long as Wehlen still holds Zille, diplomacy is paramount."

LineNo: 10133009,

Laurento Esquibel: I was just about to bring up the G...
en


"I was just about to bring up the Grand Duchy."

LineNo: 10133389,

Laurento Esquibel: Friendship Day is the 'celebration...
en


"Friendship Day is the 'celebration' that's been held in Zille each year since the treaty was signed."

LineNo: 10133491,

Lucita Azaro: Since Smolak took over, he's used...
en


"Since Smolak took over, he's used the occasion to trot out all the shiny new tanks Wehlen's oil money and United Contanan funding has bought him."

LineNo: 10133593,

Laurento Esquibel: Your presence will at the very lea...
en


"Your presence will at the very least remind him of the occupation's temporary nature."

LineNo: 10133711,

Laurento Esquibel: I know you and Duke Reinhart had a...
en


"I know you and Duke Reinhart had a rather ill-fated meeting some years ago. But it's not too late to mend those bridges."

LineNo: 10133837,

Player_Romus: I'm looking forward to it. Our nat...
en


"I'm looking forward to it. Our nations have been estranged for too long."

LineNo: 10133939,

Player_Romus: I doubt it. He knows I showed Fath...
en


"I doubt it. He knows I showed Father his letter."

LineNo: 10134041,

Player_Romus: As long as he doesn't expect too m...
en


"As long as he doesn't expect too much from me."

LineNo: 10134143,

Player_Romus: It was Father's fault. He forced m...
en


"It was Father's fault. He forced me to betray the Duke's confidence."

LineNo: 10134245,

Player_Romus: Reinhart reached out to me because...
en


"Reinhart reached out to me because he was desperate. Sooner or later, he'll come crawling back to us."

LineNo: 10134347,

Player_Romus: I still don't know why Axel even b...
en


"I still don't know why Axel even bothered. He knows full well what Rizians think of his so-called 'country'."

LineNo: 10134449,

Laurento Esquibel: I myself advised your father to sp...
en


"I myself advised your father to speak with the new Duke of Pales. To no avail, of course."

LineNo: 10134551,

Laurento Esquibel: Your father's unfortunate passing...
en


"Your father's unfortunate passing has given us a chance for a fresh start with Duke Reinhart."

LineNo: 10134653,

Laurento Esquibel: I heard he reached out to you some...
en


"I heard he reached out to you some years ago. Perhaps that connection can be built upon."

LineNo: 10134779,

Laurento Esquibel: All he expects is a warmer recepti...
en


"All he expects is a warmer reception than the one Valero gave him. Which I would recommend anyway."

LineNo: 10134881,

Laurento Esquibel: Perhaps now is our chance for a fr...
en


"Perhaps now is our chance for a fresh start."

LineNo: 10134983,

Player_Romus: I have.
en


"I have."

LineNo: 10135085,

Player_Romus: Please enlighten me.
en


"Please enlighten me."

LineNo: 10135187,

Laurento Esquibel: After years of infighting, the cou...
en


"After years of infighting, the country's left-leaning parties miraculously united in time to win this year's elections."

LineNo: 10135289,

Laurento Esquibel: The politician who managed this fe...
en


"The politician who managed this feat is now Morella's new prime minister. Alma Saltana, or as she might prefer it, *Comrade* Alma Saltana."

LineNo: 10135391,

Narrator: Hugo grimaced.
en


Hugo grimaced.

LineNo: 10135493,

Hugo Toras: Lespia and ATO are enough of a thr...
en


"Lespia and ATO are enough of a threat without the Malenyevists knocking at our back door."

LineNo: 10135619,

Laurento Esquibel: Morella doesn't stand a chance of...
en


"Morella doesn't stand a chance of entering the Contanan Security Pact. Not with its current levels of poverty."

LineNo: 10135721,

Laurento Esquibel: But there are rumors that Prime Mi...
en


"But there are rumors that Prime Minister Saltana has been arranging meetings with Valgslandian Chancellor Emmerich Hegel."

LineNo: 10135847,

Player_Romus: Didn't Rizia and Valgsland used to...
en


"Didn't Rizia and Valgsland used to be allies?"

LineNo: 10135949,

Player_Romus: I'll make him remember. By any mea...
en


"I'll make him remember. By any means necessary."

LineNo: 10136051,

Player_Romus: I'm looking forward to it. I see n...
en


"I'm looking forward to it. I see no reason why Rizia and Wehlen can't be close again."

LineNo: 10136153,

Player_Romus: I'll talk to him. Maybe we can com...
en


"I'll talk to him. Maybe we can come to a productive agreement."

LineNo: 10136255,

Player_Romus: I still don't know if he can be tr...
en


"I still don't know if he can be trusted."

LineNo: 10136357,

Player_Romus: And how are our relations with Val...
en


"And how are our relations with Valgsland at the moment?"

LineNo: 10136459,

Laurento Esquibel: I must say that their Supreme Wise...
en


"I must say that their Supreme Wiseman Jorga Azmal did not approve of our ban on Golcondist pilgrims to Rizian holy sites."

LineNo: 10136561,

Player_Romus: You think Hegel is trying to get M...
en


"You think Hegel is trying to get Morella into the CSP?"

LineNo: 10136663,

Laurento Esquibel: Neutral at best, Your Majesty.
en


"Neutral at best, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10136765,

Player_Romus: Can Morella be swayed away from Va...
en


"Can Morella be swayed away from Valgish influence?"

LineNo: 10136867,

Narrator: Laurento politely nodded.
en


Laurento politely nodded.

LineNo: 10136969,

Laurento Esquibel: It's possible. But we'd have to ha...
en


"It's possible. But we'd have to have something to offer."

LineNo: 10137071,

Laurento Esquibel: Not currently. But Valgsland throw...
en


"Not currently. But Valgsland throwing its support behind Morella's leftward turn is concerning enough."

LineNo: 10137173,

Player_Romus: You're right. Malenyev and his fol...
en


"You're right. Malenyev and his followers are the real menace."

LineNo: 10137275,

Player_Romus: Arcasian liberalism is a far worse...
en


"Arcasian liberalism is a far worse threat to our way of life than Malenyevism."

LineNo: 10137377,

Player_Romus: As long as we remain on good terms...
en


"As long as we remain on good terms with Morella, I don't care about the country's political leanings."

LineNo: 10137479,

Laurento Esquibel: As for Morella's neighbor Derdia...
en


"As for Morella's neighbor Derdia..."

LineNo: 10137671,

Laurento Esquibel: An admirable impulse. But this is...
en


"An admirable impulse. But this is unfortunately only a ceremony, not a diplomatic talk."

LineNo: 10137773,

Laurento Esquibel: Circumstances have changed since t...
en


"Circumstances have changed since the '20s, of course. But it's good that you are still holding out that hope."

LineNo: 10137875,

Laurento Esquibel: There is one more country we haven...
en


"There is one more country we haven't discussed. Rumburg."

LineNo: 10138001,

Player_Romus: Is there even anything to discuss?...
en


"Is there even anything to discuss? They're our allies."

LineNo: 10138103,

Player_Romus: Yes, how are my in-laws?
en


"Yes, how are my in-laws?"

LineNo: 10138205,

Player_Romus: I always expected Beatrice to turn...
en


"I always expected Beatrice to turn on me after Lena died. I'm amazed she's stayed allied with us."

LineNo: 10138307,

Laurento Esquibel: For the moment, Queen Beatrice and...
en


"For the moment, Queen Beatrice and her country are firmly allied with Rizia."

LineNo: 10138409,

Laurento Esquibel: Yes, for the time being, Queen Bea...
en


"Yes, for the time being, Queen Beatrice and her country are firmly allied with Rizia."

Laurento turned away from the map towards me.

LineNo: 10140297,

Laurento Esquibel: As for Morella...
en


"As for Morella..."

LineNo: 10141145,

Player_Romus: Please, continue.
en


"Please, continue."

LineNo: 10141247,

Laurento Esquibel: Of course. Queen Beatrice and her...
en


"Of course. Queen Beatrice and her country are firmly allied with Rizia."

LineNo: 10141349,

Laurento Esquibel: Our allies, Queen Beatrice and her...
en


"Our allies, Queen Beatrice and her country, are doing fine from what we're seeing."

LineNo: 10141451,

Player_Romus: In what way?
en


"In what way?"

LineNo: 10141553,

Lucita Azaro: Considering the state of Zille sin...
en


"Considering the state of Zille since it landed in Wehlen's hands, I see no point in remaining diplomatic. Have you been there lately? It's an industrial wasteland."

LineNo: 10141655,

Laurento Esquibel: Wehlen's access to Zille's land an...
en


"Wehlen's access to Zille's land and resources helped bring it out of recession after the war. Smolak will have difficulty letting go of such a valuable asset."

LineNo: 10141757,

Hugo Toras: Some argue Wehlen did little but a...
en


"Some argue Wehlen did little but accelerate the development that was already occurring in the region prior to the handover."

LineNo: 10141859,

Laurento Esquibel: Either way, Wehlen's access to Zil...
en


"Either way, Wehlen's access to Zille's land and resources helped bring it out of recession after the war. Smolak will have difficulty letting go of such a valuable asset."

LineNo: 10141961,

Player_Romus: Can we count on him to honor the t...
en


"Can we count on him to honor the terms of the treaty?"

LineNo: 10142063,

Player_Romus: Can the international community be...
en


"Can the international community be relied on to intervene if Smolak breaks a signed pact?"

LineNo: 10142165,

Player_Romus: What about the people of Zille? Su...
en


"What about the people of Zille? Surely they can't wait for the land to be returned to Rizia."

LineNo: 10142267,

Player_Romus: I will act diplomatically with Pre...
en


"I will act diplomatically with President Smolak. We can sweeten the deal if, necessary. I will appease him until we get Zille back."

LineNo: 10142369,

Laurento Esquibel: Half of the country's native Rizia...
en


"Half of the country's native Rizian population fled during the civil war. Like the Queen Mother's parents, I recall."

LineNo: 10142471,

Elena Werner: Given how many countries depend on...
en


"Given how many countries depend on Wehzek oil, either directly or indirectly, I wouldn't be so sure about that."

LineNo: 10142573,

Hugo Toras: Smolak's current focus is on eradi...
en


"Smolak's current focus is on eradicating terrorism by the Bluds, a Golcondist ethnic group native to Wehlen and Sordland. He's been very vocal about his desire for cooperation on that front."

LineNo: 10142675,

Lucita Azaro: Smolak is not as weak as he seems....
en


"Smolak is not as weak as he seems. It will take a great deal of time and effort before our firepower matches his. He may act bold."

LineNo: 10142777,

Lucita Azaro: Among those who were stubborn enou...
en


"Among those who were stubborn enough to stay, opinion is divided. We have to remember that it's been almost 25 years."

LineNo: 10142879,

Laurento Esquibel: In the meantime, any perceived agg...
en


"In the meantime, any perceived aggression on our part may only give him an excuse to break it."

LineNo: 10142981,

Lucita Azaro: The funding Wehlen has received fr...
en


"The funding Wehlen has received from United Contana may also have Smolak believing he can act with impunity."

LineNo: 10143083,

Laurento Esquibel: Not all Bluds are terrorists, Your...
en


"Not all Bluds are terrorists, Your Grace. Mr. Smolak is particularly interested in the separatist group known as the Bludish Freedom Front. Who have been rumored to be receiving support from none other than Rumburg."

LineNo: 10143185,

Player_Romus: What's that?
en


"What's that?"

LineNo: 10143287,

Player_Romus: That name's got to be some kind of...
en


"That name's got to be some kind of joke."

LineNo: 10143389,

Laurento Esquibel: President Smolak fancies himself t...
en


"President Smolak fancies himself the humorous type, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 10143491,

Laurento Esquibel: Speaking of Lyza, she's the one wh...
en


"Speaking of Lyza, she's the one who first opened trade negotiations with Sordland back when it was still a kingdom. But Soll's disdain for the monarchy kept us from continuing down that path."

LineNo: 10143593,

Laurento Esquibel: The Alphonso administration, meanw...
en


"The Alphonso administration, meanwhile, has no such qualms about royalty. In fact, his new development minister Gus Manger has already had personal business dealings in Rizia."

LineNo: 10143695,

Hugo Toras: Our friend Mr. Montoro of Rizian R...
en


"Our friend Mr. Montoro of Rizian Royal Gold has been making overtures to the Sordish oligarchy, it seems. Birds of crassly ostentatious plumage flock together."

LineNo: 10143821,

Player_Romus: I don't like your tone, Hugo. Rust...
en


"I don't like your tone, Hugo. Rusty and the Sordish oligarchs are self-made men. I respect that."

LineNo: 10143923,

Player_Romus: What does Sordland want from us?
en


"What does Sordland want from us?"

LineNo: 10144025,

Elena Werner: That hasn't been disclosed yet. Th...
en


"That hasn't been disclosed yet. The country already has abundant gas resources. They could be looking to shore up their Central Bank with gold in the wake of Alphonso's privatization spree."

LineNo: 10144127,

Laurento Esquibel: Shall I continue?
en


"Shall I continue?"

LineNo: 10144229,

Player_Romus: I'm not sure if I trust either Alp...
en


"I'm not sure if I trust either Alphonso or his minister. But I'm open to proposals."

LineNo: 10144331,

Laurento Esquibel: It would be a feat to repair our t...
en


"It would be a feat to repair our ties with Sordland. Perhaps the glory days of Lyza are not lost after all."

LineNo: 10144433,

Hugo Toras: A commoner with money is like a mo...
en


"A commoner with money is like a monkey with a wristwatch. Entertaining for a while, but what's he really going to do with it?"

LineNo: 10144535,

Player_Romus: Wealthy commoners making plans beh...
en


"Wealthy commoners making plans behind our back. It doesn't smell good."

LineNo: 10144637,

Laurento Esquibel: Ms. Werner already mentioned the l...
en


"Ms. Werner already mentioned the large amounts of gold we export to the country through their strategic Port Grim."

LineNo: 10144739,

Laurento Esquibel: We also have a deal allowing Rumbu...
en


"We also have a deal allowing Rumburg's ships priority access to our ports in Porte Drazon and Monqiz. We are, in essence, their gateway to the Antacean Sea."

LineNo: 10144841,

Lucita Azaro: Militarily speaking, the alliance...
en


"Militarily speaking, the alliance doesn't amount to much. Rumburg will supply us with arms in case of war, but neither of our countries is officially obligated to come to the other's aid."

LineNo: 10144967,

Player_Romus: What are these rumors about Rumbur...
en


"What are these rumors about Rumburg interfering in Wehlen?"

LineNo: 10145069,

Player_Romus: Is the Queen plotting anything aga...
en


"Is the Queen plotting anything against Sordland?"

LineNo: 10145171,

Laurento Esquibel: It won't be behind your back for l...
en


"It won't be behind your back for long, Your Majesty. Both Alphonso and Manger want to talk to you."

LineNo: 10145273,

Laurento Esquibel: Not a bad analogy, Your Grace. But...
en


"Not a bad analogy, Your Grace. But these are the men who hold the power in Sordland. We'll have to deal with them sooner or later."

LineNo: 10145375,

Player_Romus: Duchess Azaro mentioned Rumburg wa...
en


"Duchess Azaro mentioned Rumburg was getting closer to Arcasia."

LineNo: 10145755,

Player_Romus: I've heard that Rumburg has been g...
en
